        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>The ruling came just hours after U.S. District Judge Charles Breyer issued a temporary restraining order finding that Trump's deployment. Credits: AP Photo</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
        The Appeals court <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-13-jun-25-spotlight-h1-1-temporarily-blocked?source=website" target="_blank">temporarily halted</a> a ruling that blocked the deployment of 4,000 National Guard troops to LA, letting Trump keep control until a June 17 hearing. The judge said he would not rule on the Marines because they were not out on the streets yet. About 700 Marines are undergoing civil disturbance training at Naval Weapons Station Seal Beach in Orange County, California. 
        </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          At the same time, President Trump <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-13-jun-25-spotlight-h1-2-plans-to-revise?source=website" target="_blank">plans to revise</a> his immigration enforcement policies after admitting they have hurt the farming and hospitality sectors. He promised a “common sense” executive decree but offered no specifics. About 42% of farm workers in the US between 2020 and 2022 lacked judicial status. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
          On the other hand, Trump has launched a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-13-jun-25-spotlight-h1-3-gold-card-program?source=website" target="_blank">“Gold Card” program</a> providing US residency and a path to citizenship for a $5M payment. Over 15,000 people signed up within 24 hours. Trump asserts the program will raise funds for the federal budget, although it contradicts his ongoing immigration crackdown and travel bans.</p>
